    Search Results

    Dictionary
    Definitions from Oxford Languages · Learn more
    bag
    noun
    noun: bag; plural noun: bags; noun: one's bag; plural noun: one's bags
    1. 1.
      a flexible container with an opening at the top, used for carrying things.
      "he arrived at the children's ward carrying a bag full of toys for the young patients"
      h
      Similar:
      receptacle
      container
      shopping bag
      string bag
      sack
      carrier bag
      carrier
      poke
      keister
    2. 2.
      informal
      one's particular interest or taste.
      "ask the manager about mild curries, if that's your bag"
    verb
    verb: bag; 3rd person present: bags; past tense: bagged; past participle: bagged; gerund or present participle: bagging; noun: bagging
    1. 1.
      put (something) in a bag.
      "customers bagged their own groceries"
    2. 2.
      succeed in killing or catching (an animal).
      "Mike bagged nineteen cod"
      h
      Similar:
      catch
      capture
      trap
      snare
      ensnare
      land
      kill
      shoot
      pick off
